messages.text: Hey baby. It’s been good. Just got off for lunch. :)
Cutting through the park now to grab a bite to eat from Larry’s.
Haven’t had anything to eat since breakfast.
Didn’t you eat that sandwich I made for you this morning?
The tuna on rye with hummus?
Oh, yeah. I put it in the fridge in the break room when I got to work.
Guess I forgot it was there.
I can save it for tomorrow though.
I’m sure nobody’s gonna touch it.
Are you still walking through the park?
Is it okay if maybe you sit down or something?
I just think you should sit down maybe.
I just don’t know how else to say this.
I just feel like I’m at the end of my rope here with you.
When’s the last time you honestly ate anything I made you?
Can you answer me that, Brian?
Why are your texts coming up as unknown number now?
Found a bomb in a box underneath the bench I was sitting.
Bomb squad is on their way here.
I just told you why. There’s a bomb here.
I’m looking at it right now.
Pretty sure it’s been sitting here for a while too.
The person who made it knew what they were doing.
Wait, then what are you still doing there?!
And why did you switch phones?
Get the hell out of there.
Brian, why haven’t you left yet?
Am I even talking to you right now?
It’s going to take 5 minutes for the bomb squad to get here.
There’s 4 minutes left on the timer.
4 minutes and then it’ll all be over.
I just want to say some things to you.
Police told me I can’t call you or the bomb might go off.
I switched to my other phone that I know no one will call me on.
So please don’t call me or I’m gonna die.
But I wish we both were.
And I just wanted to say I’m sorry by the way.
For not eating anything you made lately.
You think I give a shit right now about that?
You don’t have to say sorry about anything right now.
But I just feel like I need to.
And I’m sorry what happened with Cat too.
That’s whose pictures you saw the other day on my cell.
I forgot to take pictures of her with my other phone.
I don’t care about any of this!
I don’t. None of it matters.
All I care about right now is that you’re okay.
I don’t have a lot of time left, okay?
I texted you after that frat party freshman year.
The only thing I remembered was you gave me your phone number.
The party we first met at.
It was like, what, 4 years ago, right?
We didn’t meet at a party though, babe.
We met at J.T.’s bar mitzvah.
Guess I just thought of the first happy memory I had of you.
We never went to a frat party though, Brian.
I thought it was Brad’s party?
No, we never went to any of those.
It’s hard remembering something that long ago, I guess.
Can’t say I never tried to help anybody out now, can I?
I don’t know who the hell you are.
But if you killed my husband, I hope it was quick.
